# apps/web local environment template (placeholders only)
# Copy to apps/web/.env.local.

NODE_ENV=development
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_ENV=development

# Same-origin request integrity for anonymous public mutation/read APIs.
# monitor — log failures but allow (default in non-production)
# enforce — fail closed on missing/mismatched CSRF token (default in production)
# REQUEST_INTEGRITY_MODE=monitor

# Public structured-data backend (server-side reads only):
# PUBLIC_DATA_SOURCE=seed|postgres
# PUBLIC_READ_API_DISABLED=1
# APP_PUBLIC_RELEASE_ARTIFACT_BASE_URL=
# Note: postgres mode reads bb_public.* and skips ADR-004 entities.json artifacts
# (local fixtures can be a stale smaller slice than the live catalog).
#
# Local dig (entities on map/explore/search):
#   Prefer: pnpm dev:web   (loads DATABASE_URL if present; fails fast on postgres misconfig)
#   Or set both of:
#     PUBLIC_DATA_SOURCE=postgres
#     DATABASE_URL=…          # server-only; never NEXT_PUBLIC_*
#     OPENROUTER_API_KEY=…    # server-only; operator-cli enrichment-run (see docs/research/agent-local-env.md)
#     DATABASE_SSL=1
#   Without DATABASE_URL, unset PUBLIC_DATA_SOURCE falls back to the 4-entity Dunbar seed
#   (national dig looks empty). PUBLIC_DATA_SOURCE=postgres without DATABASE_URL returns
#   an EMPTY catalog (seed is refused by design).
#
# Postgres cutover (server-only; use service_role / direct pooler URL via 1Password):
# DATABASE_URL=op://Private/<item-id>/credential
# APP_DATABASE_URL=op://Private/<item-id>/credential
# DATABASE_SSL=1
# Note: Supabase URLs often include sslmode=require. The web/admin/ops pools normalize
# that to uselibpqcompat + rejectUnauthorized:false so node-pg does not fail with
# SELF_SIGNED_CERT_IN_CHAIN and silently fall back to the 4-entity seed snapshot.

# Sibling admin console (quiet “Administration” link in the public footer):
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ADMIN_ORIGIN=http://localhost:3001
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=http://localhost:3048
